"I Kissed a Girl" is the second single from Katy Perry&#039;s album One of the Boys produced by Dr. Luke. The song was featured in one of the episodes on the first season of Gossip Girl. It quickly became a hit as the number one song on Z100 after it was first played.[1]

The song has peaked at #5 on the Billboard Hot 100, after climbing sixteen positions from the previous week, as of June 5, 2008.

A music video for the song was released on May 16th, 2008, on Katy&#039;s personal website, katyperry.com, and on MySpace. The video features a Moulin Rouge and burlesque-type setting with scenes containing Katy, along with many other flashy-dressed girls, dancing to the song. Eventually she wakes up next to her boyfriend.

The song has gained a significant amount of controversy since it became public as targeting a young audience and supporting homosexuality and bisexuality.[1] Katy Perry has stated that she is not bisexual, but that the song is about experimenting that many do as they learn who they are.
